'''''Tatooine Manhunt''''' is a [[Star Wars Legends|''Star Wars'' Legends]] adventure book for use with ''[[Star Wars: The Roleplaying Game]]''. The adventure scenario pits [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel Alliance]] agents against [[Bounty hunter/Legends|bounty hunters]] in a desperate search for the elusive hero [[Adar Tallon/Legends|Adar Tallon]] on the [[Desert/Legends|desert]] [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Tatooine/Legends|Tatooine]].

The ''Tatooine Manhunt'' set includes a double-sided color map of the [[Chalmun's Spaceport Cantina/Legends|Mos Eisley Cantina]] and [[Mos Eisley/Legends|Spaceport]], as well as a [[Star Warriors: Starfighter Combat in the Star Wars Universe|''Star Warriors'']] combat scenario with full-color counters. ''Tatooine Manhunt'' was written by [[Bill Slavicsek]] and [[Daniel Greenberg]], and published by [[West End Games]] in [[1988]].

==Publisher's summary==
''Talon, Victor of Balamak. Talon, Father of the Old Republic Navy. Talon, who shaped modern Imperial naval tactics. Statues honoring Talon stand all over the Empire &mdash; except where the Emperor pulled them down.''

''They say Talon died years ago. But they're wrong. He's still alive.''

''*The bounty on his head exceeds 50 million credits &mdash; but who offers it?''
''*The Empire wants him &mdash; but dead or alive?''
''*Bounty hunters are converging from all over the galaxy &mdash; but to protect him or hunt him?''
''*Even Jabba the Hutt is "interested" &mdash; but why?''

''Now the Rebel Alliance wants him, and the word is he's on Tatooine. Guess where you're going?''

==Plot summary==
In this adventure, a group of [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel agents]] on [[Kwenn Space Station/Legends|Kwenn Space Station]] in the [[Kwenn system/Legends|Kwenn system]]&mdash;the player characters&mdash;learn that [[Adar Tallon/Legends|Adar Tallon]], a hero of the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]] long presumed dead, is still alive on [[Tatooine/Legends|Tatooine]]. They also learn that the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]] has sent several [[Bounty hunter/Legends|bounty hunters]], including [[Jodo Kast]], [[IG-72]], and [[Zardra]], to capture or kill Tallon. The Rebels head to the desert planet, trying to reach Tallon ahead of the [[Bounty hunter/Legends|bounty hunters]] and the forces of the [[Imperial-class Star Destroyer/Legends|Imperial Star Destroyer]] [[Relentless (Dorja)|''Relentless'']].

The adventure comes with maps of [[Mos Eisley/Legends|Mos Eisley]] and the [[Chalmun's Spaceport Cantina/Legends|Mos Eisley Cantina]].

