===Cover gallery===
The cover illustration of this book was originally a piece of conceptual art created by [[Ralph McQuarrie]] for [[Star Wars: Episode V The Empire Strikes Back|''Star Wars'': Episode V ''The Empire Strikes Back'']]. The piece is titled "Scourge of the Galaxy," and depicted the bounty hunters [[Boba Fett/Legends|Boba Fett]], [[IG-88B/Legends|IG-88]], [[4-LOM/Legends|4-LOM]], [[Zuckuss/Legends|Zuckuss]] and [[Bossk/Legends|Bossk]] on [[Cloud City/Legends|Cloud City]], [[Bespin/Legends|Bespin]].<ref name="Telegraph">"[http://www.dailytelegraph.com.au/entertainment/oscar-winning-designer-and-illustrator-ralph-mcquarries-art-of-stars-and-superheoes-at-melbournes-silver-k-gallery/story-e6frexmi-1226209604887 Oscar-winning designer and illustrator Ralph McQuarrie's Art of Stars And Superheoes at Melbourne's Silver K Gallery]" in [http://www.dailytelegraph.com.au thetelegraph.com.au], [[November 30]], [[2011]]. Accessed [[September 24]], [[2013]].</ref>

The book features five bounty hunter characters which are visually similar to the ones depicted in ''The Empire Strikes Back'', based on the cover image. From right to left:
*The small [[Gand/Legends|Gand]] who looks like Zuckuss is Vytor Shrike.
*The [[IG-series]] droid is IG-72, rather than one of the [[IG-88 assassin droid/Legends|IG-88 assassin droids]]. (In fact, at this point, only one IG-88 was known.)
*The man in [[Mandalorian armor/Legends|Mandalorian armor]] was Jodo Kast, who has impersonated Boba Fett in the past.
*The [[Trandoshan/Legends|Trandoshan]] standing in for Bossk is [[Jungen]].
*The [[Protocol droid/Legends|protocol droid]] [[4-LOM/Legends|4-LOM]] does not have any clear analogue in the story. However, other [[Human/Legends|Human]] characters such as Zardra and Quist cover what could have been its role.
Although the cover suggests that all of these bounty hunters are allied (they are posing together, as if threatening a common target), most of them are foes to each other: Jodo Kast is not allied with any of the others, nor is IG-72; and Jungen and Shrike oppose both IG-72 and Kast.
